<task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="task-2023" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                              (topic pr-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic task strictTaskbody-c)   " ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Install gems with <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/bolt" class="- topic/ph "/> packages</title><shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc "> <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/bolt" class="- topic/ph "/> packages include their own copy of <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/ruby" class="- topic/ph "/>.</shortdesc><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><author type="creator" translate="no" class="- topic/author ">Kate Lopresti &lt;kate.lopresti@puppet.com&gt;</author></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context "><p class="- topic/p ">When you install gems for use with <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/bolt" class="- topic/ph "/>, use the <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph "> --user-install</codeph> flag to avoid requiring privileged access for installation. This option also enables sharing gem content with <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/puppet" class="- topic/ph "/> installations — such as when running <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">apply</codeph> on <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">localhost</codeph> — that use the same <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/ruby" class="- topic/ph "/> version.</p></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><!--Conflict between steps and step-unordered resolved using the preferB value of the stepsAndStepsUnorderedConflict parameter--><step class="- topic/li task/step "> <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To install a gem for use with <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/bolt" class="- topic/ph "/>, use the command appropriate to your operating system:&#160;</cmd> <choices class="- topic/ul task/choices "><choice class="- topic/li task/choice "><p class="- topic/p "> On <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/windows" class="- topic/ph "/> with the default install location, <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">"C:/Program Files/Puppet Labs/Bolt/bin/gem.bat" install --user-install &lt;gem&gt;</codeph> </p></choice><choice class="- topic/li task/choice ">On other platforms, <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">/opt/puppetlabs/bolt/bin/gem install --user-install &lt;gem&gt;</codeph> </choice></choices> </step></steps></taskbody></task>
